#. (itstool) path: section/title
#: C/software-metadata.page:263
msgid "How to fix incorrect safety and permissions information"
msgstr "Sådan rettes forkerte oplysninger om sikkerhed og tilladelser"

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:264
msgid ""
"The safety and permissions information for an application comes from "
"different sources depending on how the application is packaged. For "
"traditionally packaged applications, for example in RPM or DEB format, there "
"is no safety or permissions information available and nothing can be done to "
"add it to an application."
msgstr ""
"Oplysninger om sikkerhed og tilladelser for et program kommer fra "
"forskellige kilder, afhængigt af hvordan programmet distribueres. For "
"traditionelt distribuerede programmer, f.eks. i RPM- eller DEB-format, "
"findes der ingen sikkerheds- eller tilladelsesoplysninger, og der kan ikke "
"gøres noget for at tilføje dem til et program."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:265
msgid ""
"For flatpak applications, the information comes from the application’s <link "
"href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/manifests.html\">flatpak manifest</"
"link>, specifying what holes in the sandbox the application requires. Each "
"of these holes typically contributes to lowering the displayed safety level "
"of the application in <app>Software</app> — moving it from ‘safe’ to "
"‘potentially unsafe’ to ‘unsafe’."
msgstr ""
"For flatpak-programmer kommer oplysningerne fra programmets <link "
"href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/manifests.html\">flatpak-manifest</"
"link>, der angiver, hvilke huller i sandkassen programmet kræver. Hvert af "
"disse huller bidrager typisk til at sænke det viste sikkerhedsniveau for "
"programmet i <app>Software</app> — fra “sikker” til “potentielt usikker” til "
"“usikker”."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:266
msgid ""
"In order to improve the safety level of an application, its sandboxing must "
"be made as tight as possible, by removing <link href=\"https://docs.flatpak."
"org/en/latest/sandbox-permissions.html\">sandbox permissions</link> where "
"they’re not needed, and using <link href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/"
"latest/desktop-integration.html#portals\">portals</link> instead of sandbox "
"permissions where possible. Use of portals does not lower the displayed "
"safety level of an application in <app>Software</app>."
msgstr ""
"For at forbedre sikkerhedsniveauet for et program skal dets "
"sandkassetilstand gøres så streng som muligt ved at fjerne <link "
"href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/sandbox-permissions.html "
"\">sandkassetilladelser</link>, hvor de ikke er nødvendige, og ved at bruge "
"<link href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/desktop-integration."
"html#portals\">portaler</link> i stedet for sandkassetilladelser, hvor det "
"er muligt. Brug af portaler sænker ikke det viste sikkerhedsniveau for et "
"program i <app>Software</app>."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:267
msgid ""
"For example, if the application requests read/write access to the full file "
"system (<code>--filesystem=host</code>), does it actually need that, or does "
"it only need to access files in a few specific locations? If so, the <link "
"href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/desktop-integration."
"html#portals\">file portal</link> could be used, or more specific <link "
"href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/sandbox-permissions."
"html#filesystem-access\">file system permissions</link> could be specified."
msgstr ""
"Hvis programmet f.eks. anmoder om læse-/skriveadgang til hele filsystemet "
"(<code>--filesystem=host</code>), har den så virkelig brug for det, eller "
"behøver den kun at få adgang til filer på nogle få specifikke steder? I så "
"fald kan <link href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/desktop-integration."
"html#portals\">filportalen</link> bruges, eller der kan angives mere "
"specifikke <link href=\"https://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/sandbox-"
"permissions.html#filesystem-access\">filsystemtilladelser</link>."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
