"freedesktop.org/software/appstream/docs/chap-Metadata.html#tag-"
"project_license\">&lt;project_license&gt;</link> inden for programmets "
"<code>&lt;component&gt;</code> i dets metainfofil."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:301
msgid ""
"The content in this element should be an <link href=\"https://spdx.org/"
"specifications\">SPDX expression</link> which describes the ‘main’ license "
"for the project. This should typically be the license of the code, and not "
"include the license of the documentation or ancillary content."
msgstr ""
"Indholdet i dette element skal være et <link href=\"https://spdx.org/"
"specifications\">SPDX-udtryk</link>, der beskriver projektets “hovedlicens”. "
"Dette bør typisk være kildekodens licens og må ikke omfatte licensen for "
"dokumentationen eller supplerende indhold."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:302
msgid ""
"If the SPDX expression is a single license, or an ‘or’ combination of "
"multiple licenses, which are all <link href=\"https://spdx.org/licenses/"
"\">FSF or OSI approved</link>, the application is considered ‘free software’ "
"and the license tile says so. Otherwise, it’s considered ‘proprietary’."
msgstr ""
"Hvis SPDX-udtrykket er en enkelt licens eller en “eller”-kombination af "
"flere licenser, som alle er <link href=\"https://spdx.org/licenses/"
"\">godkendt af FSF eller OSI</link>, betragtes programmet som “fri "
"software”, og det fremgår af licensflisen. I modsat fald betragtes det som "
"“proprietært”."

#. (itstool) path: section/p
#: C/software-metadata.page:303
msgid ""
"If an application is being displayed as ‘proprietary’ when you think it "
"shouldn’t be, it’s likely that the <code>&lt;project_license&gt;</code> "
"element includes the documentation license for the project. Remove it."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et program vises som “proprietært”, selvom du mener, det ikke burde "
"være det, er det sandsynligt, at elementet <code>&lt;project_license&gt;</"
"code> indeholder projektets dokumentationslicens. Fjern det."

